THE VORYS AMENDMENT PROHIBITS SALE OR SHIPMENT OF ARMS NOT ONLY TO BELLIGERENTS, BUT TO OTHER NEUTRAL NATIONS WHO MAY THEMSELVES SHIP SUCH ARMS TO WARRING POWERS.  THE WOLOTT PROPOSAL FURTHER RESTRICTS AMERICAN COMMERCIAL ACTIVITIES DURING WARTIME BY PROHIBITING ANY TYPE OF FINANCIAL DEALING WITH BELLIGERENTS, OR WITH THE AGENTS OR ASSOCIATES OF BELLIGERENTS
